text:
Broadway (left midground) at Catherine Lane (center to right margin) showing at that point the old New York Life Insurance Company Building with its clock tower. The photographer is viewing northwestward from a point near Elm and Pearl Streets.

March 26, 1931

P.L. Sperr

Broadway, east side, south from Catherine Lane (left) to Worth (right) Street, showing (in background) the tower of the Municipal Building across the newly constructed taxpayer on this frontage. At the left margin is a portion of the old New York Life Insurance Company Building. To the right appears the northerly side of the 16 story Central Syndicate Building.

April 18, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
